WC [-C] [-L] [-V] [-W] [file...]Counts the number of characters, words and lines.  Words are any sequence ofcharacters separated by whitespace.  Lines are counted by counting the numberof carriage returns in the file.  Characters are counted by counting the bytesin the file that are not carriage returns.If no parameters are coded, lines, words and characters are all counted.  Ifany option - including -V - is coded, only those specified are counted.Parameters:     -C         Count characters.     -L         Count Lines.     -V         Print version number and copyright.     -W         Count words.     file       If coded, input comes from this file.  If missing, input comes                from standard in.  If more than one file name is supplied, they                are concatonated and traeted as a single input file.